    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="139"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.48/303</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of the Division of Near Eastern Affairs</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of the Iranian Trade and Economic
                        Commission</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Saleh</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-07">March 7,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Saleh</hi>: Reference is made to your letter of
                    February 24, 1942 regarding the possibility of assistance by this Government in
                    furnishing wheat for Iran. As you are aware as a result of subsequent
                    conversations with you regarding this matter, the question which you have raised
                    is being given careful consideration.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wallace Murray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
